statusbot/bot.py.message:
Nah, this is fine, I just wasn't sure if the point of this function was to guard against a missing section raising configparser.NoSectionError but now that I play with it a bit more I see that a missing option even raises configparser.NoOptionError as well. However the entire function could simply be:

    return config.get(section, name, fallback=None)

The fallback keyword argument seems to be sufficient to avoid both exceptions. This probably makes the convenience wrapper itself a questionable bit of added complexity.

